The paper deals with a hybrid automatic repeat request (HARQ) scheme for polar codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the optimization of parameter configurations, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of Rayleigh fading channels and the analysis of throughput efficiency can be related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a new scheme that has advantages over existing techniques, which can be considered as a contribution to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
